          "name": "Present Simple",
          "content": "<h2>When to use Present Simple</h2> <p>Use <strong>Present Simple</strong> for habits, routines, and facts.</p> <h3>Statements</h3> <ul> <li><strong>I/You/We/They</strong> + base verb: <em>I work</em>, <em>They study</em></li> <li><strong>He/She/It</strong> + verb + <strong>-s</strong>: <em>She works</em>, <em>He studies</em></li> </ul> <blockquote> <p><strong>Tip:</strong> verbs ending in <em>-y</em> often change to <em>-ies</em>: <em>study → studies</em>.</p> </blockquote> <h3>Questions</h3> <p>Use <strong>Do/Does</strong> + subject + base verb:</p> <ul> <li><em>Do you work?</em></li> <li><em>Does she work?</em></li> </ul>"
